I got pretty stumped by this. If anyone is anyone is stumped by this, the way timotheus' representation is written here did not work for me but the way he put it in  https://github.com/timotheus/ebaysdk-python/wiki/Request-Dictionary actually made the most sense and worked. so instead of:

{'productId': {'@attrs': {'type': 'upc'}, '#text':'710425495243'}}

I did:

{'productId': { '#text': 710425495243,'@attrs': {'type': 'UPC'}}}

I want to reiterate that the second link he posted: http://developer.ebay.com/devzone/finding/callref/finditemsbyproduct.html#Request.productId

helped me understand why this is the way it is much better.

