@manojItela The reason for this is because you are naming your `AWS::Serverless::Api` the same as the SAM generated one ([ServerlessRestApi](https://github.com/awslabs/serverless-application-model/blob/master/docs/internals/generated_resources.rst#api))

We are working on reversing the behavior we added, since this did break for people and we do not have good documentation around not using our generated Resource's Logical Id. In the future, you should avoid naming conflicts with SAM to ensure things like this do not happen. 

One work around that I know of (other than to wait for us to deploy the patch), is to change the name of the logical id of your `AWS::Serverless::Api` and update any references. **IMPORTANT!! DO NOTE** this will **create** new resources!!! There may be others but nothing is directly coming to mind at the moment.

